<subSubSection id="6EB90F3483F180F622493DDAE714DD74" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="EA1EDC873C1B83C37043B09F0A2EE237" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E063ED041D603CF484690A52B585D251" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">
After the study of type material, the number of marginal papillae is not defined for 
<taxonomicName id="76628EA254921967DE63E092975F9DC2" genus="S." lsidName="S. wassi" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="wassi">
<emphasis id="7072354CB7EBF2CC7B69EECA63B92163" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">S. wassi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pettibone, 1966. Their number might be the same as in 
<taxonomicName id="625E4E89CA3CFDD408E309F1C72698EC" genus="S." lsidName="S. ligneroi" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" rank="species" species="ligneroi">
<emphasis id="B8C41E6B5F0F2E61351828AED7A8D331" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="21">S. ligneroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. described above, but better specimens are needed to clarify this. On the other hand, most diagnostic features for the species were confirmed by 
<bibRefCitation id="96C21E9BE596E7F2088B6145C3A3706D" author="Wolf, PS" journalOrPublisher="American Museum Novitates" pageId="0" pageNumber="21" publicationUrl="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/3248995" refId="B56" refString="Wolf, PS, 1984. .https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/3248995" url="https://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/3248995" year="1984">Wolf (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, the fragility of anal cirri might explain why they were not observed by him.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
